  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "情感捷思 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-affect-heuristic",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / emotion / risk / judgment</p>\n    <h1>情感捷思</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Affect Heuristic</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">當一件事讓你本能地覺得好或壞，這份情感印象常會連帶改寫你對它的風險與收益判斷，即使你以為自己只是在分析事實。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『我就是直覺覺得不對』和『情感已經在替我先做風險計分』拆開，因為很多風險判斷其實是感覺先行、分析後補。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>風險判斷 / 快速直覺</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>People use feelings as a shortcut for judging risk and benefit</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>情感印象、風險感、收益感、資訊覆寫</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在高不確定判斷裡更早察覺情感印象正在怎麼塑形風險評估</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>好感</span>\n      <span>風險</span>\n      <span>捷徑</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>很多時候，我們不是先算風險再感覺，而是先感覺再替風險找理由</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">情感捷思讓風險判斷變快，也讓它很容易被外觀、語氣與印象牽走。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>情感能快速整合複雜線索，但若把喜惡直接當成風險指標，就容易高估討厭事物的危險、低估喜歡事物的代價。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先分辨感受和證據</strong>\n        <p>直覺有價值，但它不是證據本身。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再檢查喜惡是否在帶動風險分數</strong>\n        <p>你是否因為喜歡就覺得好處多、風險小，或反過來？</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後補上慢速驗證</strong>\n        <p>越是情緒強的題目，越需要額外拉回資料和基準。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一個你第一眼就很想說『這感覺不對』的情境開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">情感捷思在安全、公共政策、產品印象與人際判斷裡都極常見。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>某新方案的外觀與措辭讓人很有戒心，於是大家立刻覺得它風險高；另一個熟悉方案看起來討喜，風險就自然被低估。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>感覺本身不是錯，麻煩在於它常會偷拿走分析的位置。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">先形成好惡印象</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">印象連動風險與收益判斷</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">分析常變成替感覺補理由</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>情感捷思最值得注意的，不是情緒會出現，而是情緒常偽裝成客觀風險直覺。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看情感捷徑的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">當你很快就知道自己喜不喜歡某方案時，也值得問自己這份喜惡正在改寫什麼。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>第一印象來源</strong>\n        <p>是外觀、名稱、說話者、品牌，還是真正的機制資訊？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>風險收益聯動</strong>\n        <p>你是否因為覺得它好，就同時覺得風險低、收益高？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>情緒強度</strong>\n        <p>情感越強烈，越需要補慢速分析。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>反向測試</strong>\n        <p>如果同內容換一個包裝，你的判斷會不會變？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>情境</th>\n            <th>情感捷思看起來像</th>\n            <th>可能造成什麼</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>新技術評估</td>\n            <td>我直覺就不信</td>\n            <td>把陌生感誤讀成高風險</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>品牌判斷</td>\n            <td>這家感覺專業</td>\n            <td>把好感誤讀成低風險</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>人際合作</td>\n            <td>我不喜歡他講話方式</td>\n            <td>把風格不合直接翻成能力或可信度問題</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼感覺這麼容易替我們先下結論</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為在複雜世界裡，情感是一種極快的壓縮器，能先給出方向感。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>快而省力</strong>\n        <p>情感能在資訊不全時快速幫你形成初步立場。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>喜惡會一體化</strong>\n        <p>喜歡某物時，連帶容易覺得它其他面向也比較好。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>討厭感會擴散</strong>\n        <p>一旦被某點觸發反感，風險評分常整體上升。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">情感捷思不是要被消滅，而是要被知道它什麼時候已經坐到駕駛座上。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把慢速驗證帶回風險評估與設計評審</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程與產品團隊來說，情感捷思會讓技術、品牌與人際印象偷偷影響本該更可證明的風險判斷。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>技術評估</strong>\n        <p>對陌生方案的戒心有時更多來自缺乏熟悉，而不全是客觀風險。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>安全審查</strong>\n        <p>說法嚇人的風險容易被高估，包裝友善的風險則可能被放鬆。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>評審互動</strong>\n        <p>對某人一開始的好惡會滲進你對他提案品質的感受。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>遇到第一眼很喜歡或很反感的方案時，最好額外補一輪結構化比較。</li>\n      <li>如果換掉名稱、包裝或說話者，你的風險評分大幅改變，那通常不是內容自己在動。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">情感捷思不是說情緒沒價值，而是說情緒常在你以為自己只在算風險時悄悄介入。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要情緒強就是錯</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>情緒可能是訊號，但不能直接當結論。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>理工場景就不會有</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>技術評估與事故判斷同樣受印象與好惡影響。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>知道這件事就能完全切開</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不能，但你可以多設反向測試與結構化對照。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我是在評估機制，還是在評估自己對它的感覺</h2>\n      </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>若把這個方案換個品牌、名字或說話者，我還會給同樣風險分數嗎</strong>\n        <p>這能測出印象影響有多大。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>我現在列出的風險與收益，有多少是真機制，有多少只是情緒推論延伸</strong>\n        <p>把兩者分開通常很有幫助。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 risk perception、availability heuristic 與 dual-process theory。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 affect heuristic 為主，再把概念帶回風險判斷、技術評估與印象形成。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Affect heuristic 條目整理了情感如何作為風險與收益判斷的快速捷徑。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Affect_heuristic\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Affect Heuristic</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>風險背景</strong>\n        <p>Risk perception 條目可作為對照，理解人如何主觀感受危險。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk_perception\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Risk Perception</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>近鄰偏誤</strong>\n        <p>Availability heuristic 有助於理解快速判斷如何受可得性與情緒共同塑形。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Availability_heuristic\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Availability Heuristic</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以挑一個你第一眼就有強烈好惡的方案，刻意把包裝拿掉只看機制，再重評一次。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
